DURBAN - The South African Weather Service has warned of severe thunderstorms expected over northern and western parts of KWaZulu-Natal on Thursday. 

 

 According to SAWS, rain has also been predicted for most of the day. 

 


 
 


 

 At least a 60 percent chance of rainfall is expected over areas including Durban, Mooi River, Pietermaritzburg, Richards Bay and Margate. 

 


 
 


 Meanwhile, several road accidents have been reported in Durban. Motorists are urged to drive slower and keep their headlights on. With so many intersections having no working traffic lights due to loadshedding, drivers are urged to be cautious.

 

